This chapter introdues most of the basic elements of C++:types,
variables, expressions, statesments, and functions. along the way,
we will briefly explain how to complie and execute a program.
	After having read this chapter and worked through the exercises,
you sould be able to write, complie and execute simple programs.
Later chapters will assume that you can use the features introduced in this
chapter, and will explain these features in more detail.
